main event: A witness observed a large, slightly bluish-white object that moved at a high rate of speed and then disappeared from view.
interesting points: The object appeared to be slightly larger than a large star.
The sighting occurred on August 16, 1965 at around 7:35 PM near Little Rock, Arkansas.
The witness was interested in reporting the unusual sighting and requested report forms.
The Air Force evaluated the sighting and attributed it to an illusion or a meteorological condition, stating there were no unusual features indicating the presence of an unusual aircraft.
The report was evaluated by Colonel Eric T. de Jonckheere, Deputy for Technology and Subsystems at the Air Force.
photographs: no photographs included in the report
